::{{DIcon|Talk}} Are you ready to talk about Tribbie now?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504037332-->
:::'''Pasithea:''' ...
:::'''Pasithea:''' After reminiscing on that memory, I somewhat... understand Lady Tribbie.
:::'''Pasithea:''' As a Holy Maiden of Janusopolis, Lady Tribbie made a choice contrary to mine.
:::'''Pasithea:''' I don't know what she went through, but I'm guessing... it must have been a heavy past that renders one's teeth clenched and one's mouth speechless.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are you still avoiding them now?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504037337-->
:::'''Pasithea:''' Yes... If I were honest with myself, I still can't relinquish my complicated feelings towards Lady Tribbie. Maybe after today, there might come a chance to talk with them about what happened...
:::'''Pasithea:''' But for now, I am unable to do so.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I want to hear about your hometown.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504037340-->
:::'''Pasithea:''' Janusopolis... is my home. That is all.
:::'''Pasithea:''' I once heard of Janusopolis' glorious past during her height of power. As an essential Council venue within the Okhema Alliance, Janusopolis was once a prosperous and peaceful city.
:::'''Pasithea:''' Each time a prophecy was sought, the Temple of the Three Fates would host a grand banquet, where even civilians could gaze their eyes upon the solemn figure of the Holy Maiden from the peripheries.
:::'''Pasithea:''' But I could not experience any of that. When I was born, the Chrysos War had already begun. In times of chaos, even the grandest cities cannot escape decline. Janusopolis' people had to eat dirt to stave off hunger during the famine...
:::'''Pasithea:''' And now... she is completely gone, turned into a cold, unfathomable abyss.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Revisit the celestial echoes of the past.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504037346-->
:::'''Pasithea:''' I never expected you to be so nostalgic for that city's past... Then let Oronyx reenact for you those years gone by.
