:;([[#Gallery|Cutscene]] plays)
:::The sound of collapse and cries... They are sounds I'll never forget &mdash; the haunting echoes of the black tide.
:::At that time, I cowered in the temple, waiting for {{Rubi|Thanatos|Death}} to lead me from my bitterness to their river.
:::But... what arrived was a group of fugitives, guided by Oronyx, seeking an oracle from the Holy Maiden.
:::O destiny, I scream at thee &mdash; To hell with the Holy Maiden! I am nothing but a blind woman now!
:::Yet...
:::Like the priests, I forged an oracle. In the darkness, I clung to my childhood memories, barely piecing together the path that would lead to Okhema.
:::Then, I pointed to the sky and said to them &mdash;
:::Move ahead! The Time Titan has delivered a prophecy. We shall overcome the barriers of death and reach the holy city of Kephale!
:;(Cutscene ends)
